{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9dba8df7-3a74-4f88-9170-70f47d3fa494","content":"Two changes in your project file:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the VSTest opt-in:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- delete this line -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. **Keep** (or update) the SDK version — 3.8.0 already defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is absent:\n   ```xml\n   <Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n   ```\n\nThat's it. Starting with MSTest.Sdk **3.4+**, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner. The `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property was the only thing forcing the old runner. Removing it switches you over.\n\n### What to expect after the change\n\n| Area | Notes |\n|---|---|\n| **`dotnet test`** | Works the same; the SDK wires up the new platform automatically. |\n| **CLI options** | Some VSTest CLI switches (e.g. `--logger`) change syntax. Run `dotnet test -- --help` to see the new options. |\n| **Runsettings** | `.runsettings` files are still supported but some adapter-specific nodes may need updating. |\n| **CI / TRX output** | Add `--results-directory` and `--report-trx` if your pipeline relied on TRX loggers. |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"48c7d466-4851-46c0-9cd1-f7b0e06214f2","outputTokens":339,"requestId":"4C3D:1F8B8F:D776E4:10BA286:6A0129BC"},"id":"a8de287c-169a-44e5-8b6a-f4c202919f4b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:58:46.689Z","parentId":"9879b8f6-4a93-4353-bf3a-62e13d8efee7"}
